Acute thrombosis of the renal transplant artery: a case report and review of the literature.
 Acute thrombosis of the renal transplant artery is a known but unusual complication of renal transplantation usually occurring in the first month.
 Reported here is a case of acute renal artery thrombosis in a well functioning long-term renal allograft in which there was clear angiographic evidence of a normal renal artery two years earlier.
